{"parentUuid":"192b0391-2b7c-4a03-963b-d26aeb171684","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"5ef7c265-01bf-43e0-a0ae-2f6f6b58bffb","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":" # Note: some providers (Matter, Virtual) only return slots already\n        # configured in a Lock Code Manager config entry, so unmanaged codes\n        # on those providers will not be detected here. This reset step is\n        # most useful for Z-Wave locks which return all occupied slots.\n\nthat's something we choose isn't it? At least for matter, we can know which slots have been setup already"},"uuid":"58dccf0b-f8c8-4cc9-aad2-782fd736ed89","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:28:19.960Z","permissionMode":"bypassPermissions","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"58dccf0b-f8c8-4cc9-aad2-782fd736ed89","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TvdCCARwgVVmshGRNktt39","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYou're right. The Matter provider's `async_get_usercodes` currently filters to only configured slots:\n\n```python\ncode_slots = {\n    int(code_slot)\n    for entry in self.hass.config_entries.async_entries(DOMAIN)\n    for code_slot in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_SLOTS, {})\n    if self.lock.entity_id in get_entry_data(entry, CONF_LOCKS, [])\n}\n```\n\nBut `get_lock_users` returns *all* users/credentials on the lock — we just choose to filter them down. For the lock reset step, we'd want the unfiltered view.\n\nThe options are:\n\n**A) Add a `get_all_usercodes` method** to BaseLock that returns all slots (not filtered by config). Providers override it. The lock reset step calls this instead of `async_get_usercodes`.\n\n**B) Change `async_get_usercodes` to return all occupied slots** and let callers filter. This would change the coordinator's behavior though — it'd suddenly have data for slots it doesn't manage.\n\n**C) Pass a flag** like `include_unmanaged=True` to `async_get_usercodes`.\n\nA is cleanest — separate method, clear intent, no impact on existing sync flow. But this is a broader change that affects the provider interface. Want me to add it now as part of this PR, or make it a follow-up?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":220,"cache_read_input_tokens":344791,"output_tokens":347,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":220,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjX765xWnwPMnELKYmCh","type":"assistant","uuid":"a3f5e2d0-bf54-4e76-8912-89bf1c014c43","timestamp":"2026-04-04T22:28:36.141Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
