n......................................(no files to check)Skipped\nyamllint.............................................(no files to check)Skipped\nmarkdownlint.............................................................Passed\nflake8...............................................(no files to check)Skipped\nmypy.................................................(no files to check)Skipped\nLint GitHub Actions workflow files...................(no files to check)Skipped\n[feat/lock-reset-step 78d92cc] Update TODO: lock reset step for options flow\n 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n[entire] Pushing entire/checkpoints/v1 to origin... done\nTo https://github.com/raman325/lock_code_manager.git\n   7d330c7..78d92cc  feat/lock-reset-step -> feat/lock-reset-step","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d1f4f768-27b2-4d6b-9401-15fca018f584","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
{"parentUuid":"4c31e7d6-db1e-4edf-98dd-9292ff3893f1","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HCFCk1j8E1x4sR26bwYrsg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Right — in the options flow, existing managed slots would appear in `async_get_usercodes` results, but they're managed by *this* entry. The `_async_get_unmanaged_codes` filter (`find_entry_for_lock_slot` / `managed_slots` check) would correctly exclude them since they're already managed. But if a slot was removed from the entry in the same options update and then the lock reset runs, it would appear as \"unmanaged\" even though the user just removed it intentionally.\n\nThat's the key nuance for the options flow: the lock reset check needs to compare against the *new* slot config (what the user is submitting), not the *current* stored config. Otherwise removing a slot from an entry could trigger \"unmanaged code found\" for the slot you just removed.\n\nThis is captured in the TODO. For now the lock reset only runs in the initial setup flow where there's no pre-existing config to conflict with."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":715,"cache_read_input_tokens":393448,"output_tokens":217,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":715,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZjaHMRpSjUzdai3Lxgjr","type":"assistant","uuid":"e4ed2834-1ffb-412b-9767-133b8ba80b01","timestamp":"2026-04-04T23:10:15.566Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/raman/projects/lock_code_manager","sessionId":"3f097ff1-5bb6-4622-8cfe-35782dd270ba","version":"2.1.81","gitBranch":"feat/lock-reset-step","slug":"jolly-wandering-moonbeam"}
